    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on high-upside matchups today, headlined by the elite 83.29 rating of **Gunnar Henderson**. Facing Ryne Nelson, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive park-factor boost (+16%) and wind assistance that should inflate his potential for extra-base hits; his 10% order premium as the leadoff man makes him the cornerstone of today\u2019s production. Joining him in the upper echelon is **Kyle Tucker** (72.71), whose elite xwOBA profile and wind-aided matchup against David Peterson solidify his status as an essential start. **Josh Lowe** also projects favorably at 66.41; despite a lower lineup spot, his dynamic platoon advantage against Will Warren and favorable park conditions provide a high-floor opportunity to chase the stolen bases we desperately need.\n\nPlatoon edges remain a driving force behind our marginal lineup decisions, particularly for **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.23) and **Andy Pages** (63.77). For **Luis Robert Jr.**, the combination of a favorable platoon and the slow delivery of Justin Wrobleski enhances his stolen base probability, while **Andy Pages** rides a +6% order bump and positive wind conditions to clear the 60-point \"Strong\" threshold. The closest decision on our bench involved **Marcell Ozuna** (52.88). While **Marcell Ozuna** possesses significant power, he narrowly missed the cut because the optimizer favored the high-floor, platoon-benefited efficiency of **Nolan Schanuel** (58.19) in the Utility slot, as **Nolan Schanuel** avoids the negative park variance currently impacting **Marcell Ozuna**.\n\nRisks persist across the board as every projected lineup position remains \"Pending.\" We must exercise caution with **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (53.78) and **Jorge Polanco** (51.23); both face the significant hurdle of Paul Skenes and Justin Wrobleski, respectively. The heavy negative SP skill modifiers (-19% for both) keep these players in the \"Marginal\" range despite their order benefits. Furthermore, while **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks** hold respectable scores in the mid-50s, their value is heavily tied to the assumption that they will secure spots in the top half of their lineups; any demotion in the official lineup card could quickly push them below our acceptable performance floor.",
